In [Creating Release Notes|https://confluence.atlassian.com/adminjiracloud/creating-release-notes-776636314.html/], it mentioned the following:

{quote}
At present, two example format templates are provided - HTML and Text - using Velocity templates. Further format templates can be created and added to the system.
{quote}

In Jira Cloud, there is no way to create/add a new Release Note template. The above is incorrect and misleading and it would be great to remove/edit the last sentence.

h3. Problem Statement
People page on Projects is empty

h3. Steps to replicate
# Create Project
# Go to People 
# People Page Empty

h3. Dev Console
{code}
users-and-roles.d5562f81046474b39ede.5.js:1 Uncaught (in promise) Error: Failed to obtain the project context for the page
    at users-and-roles.d5562f81046474b39ede.5.js:1
    at <anonymous>
{code}
Sources
{code}
{
        log.safeError('users-and-roles.entry', 'Failed to fetch the project context');
        throw Error('Failed to obtain the project context for the page');
    }
{code}

h3. Workaround
No Workaround

